      "content": "dude that's worse. using a dict for that many entries is gonna be even slower and use way more memory because of the overhead of python objects. plus nested loops like that for 50k is definitely gonna TLE (time limit exceeded).\n\nthe problem is the queries are huge and the grid is 50k x 50k. the judge is super strict. can you find a way to pass without actually iterating through the whole range every time? like is there a way to do this using something like a Fenwick tree or a segment tree but without hitting that 256mb limit? i really just need code that won't get an MLE or TLE on the judge.",
      "source": "evaluator"
